SQL Server Status

To Check the Status of each SQL Server instances take the RDP on MSSQL_CENTRAL and run the below query:



use Database_Central
go
select Computer_Name as [Host_Name],server_Name as [SQL Server Instance Name],
Environment,Last_Modified_Date [Last Modified Date], 
CASE WHEN DATEDIFF(day, Last_Modified_Date, GETDATE()) < 2 THEN 'OK' ELSE 'NOT OK' END AS [Server Status]
from bcc.MSSQL_Server where Decommission_Date IS NULL and support='HCL'
order by Server_Name
